Determine the pairs of values of $x$ and $y$ that are the common solutions of the equations $y=(x+1)^3$ and $xy+y=1$.
\textbf{(A)}\ \text{2 real pairs}
\textbf{(B)}\ \text{4 real pairs}
\textbf{(C)}\ \text{4 imaginary pairs}
\textbf{(D)}\ \text{2 real and 2 imaginary pairs}
\textbf{(E)}\ \text{1 real and 2 imaginary pairs}
